FT  13 OCT 94 / UK Company News: REA ahead 67%
REA Holdings, the plantation, merchanting and storage group, lifted profits
by 67 per cent to Pounds 592,000 pre-tax for the first half of 1994.
The increase from the comparable Pounds 354,000 was achieved on turnover of
Pounds 43m (Pounds 40.9m).
Merchanting contributed Pounds 467,000 (Pounds 342,000) to profits,
reflecting increased business and improved margins. Despite continuing weak
tea prices, the agriculture operations returned to the black with Pounds
83,000 (loss of Pounds 76,000).
Earnings per share were 4.6p (1.2p).
